.nh
.TH "prayertime-cli" "1" "Mar 2026" "prayertime-cli" ""

.SH NAME
prayertime-cli-locations - Search locations before requesting prayer times


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBprayertime-cli locations [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Search and inspect candidate places before requesting prayer times.

.PP
Contract:
  - --query is required.
  - Use --country-code to narrow ambiguous place names.
  - --output text prints numbered candidates for humans.
  - --output json prints structured candidates with display_name, coordinates, and timezone.
  - Success payloads go to stdout. Errors go to stderr unless --output json is used.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for locations


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--json\fP[=false]
	Shortcut for --output json

.PP
\fB--output\fP="text"
	Output mode: text, json, or value


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBprayertime-cli(1)\fP, \fBprayertime-cli-locations-search(1)\fP
